headline.main: HOSPITAL ON OAHU FIRST USED DEC. 7; Navy Medical Staff Building It on Hawaiian Hillside When Japanese Struck BEDS SET UP UNDER FIRE Physicians Prominent Here in Civilian Life Among Officers at Now Big Institution

lead_paragraph: HONOLULU, May 2 -- Last Fall a ship left New York Harbor with 8,621 huge boxes, a group of Navy technical men and a few Navy physicians aboard. Some of the physicians were distinguished specialists who had only recently donned uniforms.
